# Contributing to Mosaic

We welcome contributions! Please follow these guidelines to help us maintain a high-quality codebase.

## Quick Start

1. Fork the repository
2. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feature/my-feature`
3. Make your changes
4. Run tests: `flutter test`
5. Submit a pull request

## Development Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/mosaic.git
cd mosaic
flutter pub get
dart pub global activate --source path .
flutter test
```

## Guidelines

### Code Style
- Follow [Effective Dart](https://dart.dev/guides/language/effective-dart) guidelines
- Run `dart format` before committing
- Use descriptive variable and function names

### Testing
- Add tests for new features
- Ensure all tests pass before submitting
- Maintain existing test coverage

### Pull Requests
- Create an issue first for significant changes
- Include clear commit messages
- Update documentation if needed
- Link to related issues

### Bug Reports
Include:
- Clear description of the issue
- Steps to reproduce
- Flutter/Dart version
- Code sample demonstrating the bug

### Feature Requests
Include:
- Description of the proposed feature
- Use case and motivation
- Proposed implementation approach

## Need Help?

- Open an issue for questions
- Check existing issues and discussions
- Review the README for usage examples

Thank you for contributing!
